Package: gnuplot
Version: 3.8h.0
Revision: 9
Maintainer: Jeffrey Whitaker <jsw@cdc.noaa.gov>
Depends: readline-shlibs (>= 4.3-5), libpng-shlibs, texinfo, aquaterm (>= 0.3.0a-4)
BuildDepends: readline (>= 4.3-5), libpng
Source: ftp://ftp.gnuplot.vt.edu/pub/gnuplot/testing/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 0058a1a9a33fee94750c436562d297b4
Source2: ftp://ftp.gnuplot.vt.edu/pub/gnuplot/%n.pdf.gz
Source3: ftp://ftp.gnuplot.vt.edu/pub/gnuplot/gpcard.pdf.gz
Patch: %f.patch
PatchScript: <<
 cp -f %p/share/aquaterm/gnuplot/aquaTerm.trm src
 (cd ..; gunzip *gz) 
<<
NoSetCPPFLAGS: True
ConfigureParams: --without-gd --mandir='${prefix}/share/man' --with-readline=gnu --enable-mouse --enable-pm3d
CompileScript: (export CPPFLAGS=-I%p/include; ./configure %c; make)
InstallScript: <<
 make install prefix=%i
 (cd docs; make html)
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n/tutorial
 cp ../gpcard.pdf ../gnuplot.pdf docs/gnuplot.html %i/share/doc/%n
 cp -R demo %i/share/doc/%n
 cp tutorial/*plt tutorial/*dat tutorial/*tex %i/share/doc/%n/tutorial
 mkdir -p %i/Applications
 mv %i/bin/gnuplot %i/bin/gnuplotx
 echo '#!/bin/csh' > %i/bin/gnuplot
 echo 'setenv GNUTERMAPP %p/Applications/AquaTerm.app' >> %i/bin/gnuplot
 echo 'if (! $?DISPLAY) setenv GNUTERM aqua' >> %i/bin/gnuplot
 echo '%p/bin/gnuplotx' >> %i/bin/gnuplot
 chmod 755 %i/bin/gnuplot
<<
DocFiles: ANNOUNCE-MOUSE BUGS INSTALL FAQ README NEWS ChangeLog Copyright
Description: Command-driven interactive plotting program
DescDetail: <<
It can be used to plot functions and data points in both two- and 
three-dimensional plots in many different formats, and will accommodate
many of the needs of today's scientists for graphic data representation.
<<
DescPort: <<
Uses Per Persson's aqua terminal (installed via the aquaterm package).

Uses fake config.cache to trick configure into thinking there is
no tetex.
<<
